This paper deals with the indexing of trajectories of moving objects, which is a common problem in database systems (cs.DB) and data structures (cs.DS). The proposed approach involves the use of a compact data structure, which is a common topic in information retrieval (cs.IR) and compression (cs.SI). Finally, the paper also mentions the use of spatial indexes, which is a topic in computational geometry (cs.CG) and natural language processing (cs.CL). However, since the focus of the paper is on the indexing of trajectories, we consider cs.DB and cs.DS to be the most likely categories.
